credit.credit-words: Thy goodness we praise; Thy Son thou hast given to die in our place. He came from above Our curse to remove, He hath loved, he hath loved us, because he would love.
Love moved him to die, And on this we rely, He hath loved, he hath loved us, we cannot tell why. But this we can tell, He hath loved us so well, As to lay down his life to redeem us from hell.
O how shall we praise Or worthily sing thy unspeakable grace? Nothing else will we know In our journey below, But singing thy grace to thy paradise go.
Nay, and when we remove To the mansions above, Our heaven shall be still to sing of thy love. We all shall commend The love of our Friend, For ever beginning what never shall end.
